developer_understanding_on_working: The configuration code is a method that returns the alternate style-sheet title for a user agent. It first checks if the alternate style-sheet title is stored in the hints map, and if so, returns it. If not found, it falls back to the super class method to get the alternate style-sheet title.
developer_understanding_on_triggering_fr: The configuration is triggered whenever the getAlternateStyleSheet() method is called in the system. The frequency of triggering depends on how often this method is invoked in the codebase.
developer_understanding_on_size_impact: The impact of the ALTERNATE_STYLESHEET configuration option is limited to the functionality related to the alternate style-sheet title. It does not have a significant impact on the overall system performance or behavior.
